79 template <typename T> class handle_traits {};
80 
94 template <typename T, typename traits=handle_traits<T>> class handle {
95 private:
96  static mkldnn_status_t dummy_destructor(T){ return mkldnn_success; }
97 
98  std::shared_ptr<typename std::remove_pointer<T>::type> _data;
99  handle(const handle &&) = delete;
100  handle &operator=(const handle &&other) = delete;
101 protected:
102  bool operator==(const T other) const { return other == _data.get(); }
103  bool operator!=(const T other) const { return !(*this == other); }
104 public:
108  handle(T t, bool weak = false): _data(0) {
109  reset(t, weak);
110  }
111 
121  handle(): handle((T)0, true) {}
122 
123  handle(const handle &other): _data(other._data) {}
124  handle &operator=(const handle &other) {
125  _data = other._data;
126  return *this;
127  }
131  void reset(T t, bool weak = false) {
132  _data.reset(t, weak ? &dummy_destructor : traits::destructor);
133  }
134 
136  T get(bool allow_emtpy = false) const {
137  T result = _data.get();
138 
139  if (allow_emtpy == false && result == nullptr)
140  throw mkldnn::error(mkldnn_invalid_arguments,
141  "attempt to use uninitialized object");
142 
143  return result;
144  }
145 
146  bool operator==(const handle &other) const { return other._data.get() == _data.get(); }
147  bool operator!=(const handle &other) const { return !(*this == other); }
148 };

409 #define MKLDNN_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(enum_name) \
410 inline enum_name operator|(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
411  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
412  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
413 } \
414  \
415 inline enum_name operator&(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
416  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
417  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
418 } \
419  \
420 inline enum_name operator^(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
421  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
422  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
423 } \
424  \
425 inline enum_name& operator|=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
426  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
427  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
428  return lhs; \
429 } \
430  \
431 inline enum_name& operator&=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
432  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
433  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
434  return lhs; \
435 } \
436  \
437 inline enum_name& operator^=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
438  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
439  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
440  return lhs; \
441 } \
442  \
443 inline enum_name operator~(enum_name rhs) { \
444  return static_cast<enum_name>(~static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
445 } \

1339  struct desc {
1340  friend struct memory;
1342  mkldnn_memory_desc_t data;
1343 
1345  desc(): data() {}
1346 
1352  desc(const dims &adims, data_type adata_type, format_tag aformat_tag) {
1353  validate_dims(adims);
1354  error::wrap_c_api(mkldnn_memory_desc_init_by_tag(&data,
1355  (int)adims.size(),
1356  adims.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &adims[0],
1357  convert_to_c(adata_type), convert_to_c(aformat_tag)),
1358  "could not initialize a memory descriptor by tag");
1359  }
1360 
1366  desc(const dims &adims, data_type adata_type, const dims &astrides) {
1367  validate_dims(adims);
1368  error::wrap_c_api(mkldnn_memory_desc_init_by_strides(&data,
1369  (int)adims.size(),
1370  adims.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &adims[0],
1371  convert_to_c(adata_type),
1372  astrides.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &astrides[0]),
1373  "could not initialize a memory descriptor by strides");
1374  }
1375 
1379  desc(const mkldnn_memory_desc_t &adata): data(adata) {}
1380 
1382  //
1385  desc submemory_desc(const dims &adims, const dims &offsets) {
1386  mkldnn_memory_desc_t sub_md;
1387  error::wrap_c_api(mkldnn_memory_desc_init_submemory(&sub_md,
1388  &data, &adims[0], &offsets[0]),
1389  "could not initialize a sub-memory");
1390  return desc(sub_md);
1391  }
1392 
1395  size_t get_size() const { return mkldnn_memory_desc_get_size(&data); }
1396 
1398  bool is_zero() const { return data.ndims == 0; }
1399 
1400  bool operator==(const desc &other) const {
1401  return mkldnn_memory_desc_equal(&data, &other.data) != 0;
1402  }
1403 
1404  bool operator!=(const desc &other) const { return !operator==(other); }
1405  };
1406 
1407  memory() = default;
1408 
1414  memory(const desc &md, const engine &aengine, void *ahandle) {
1415  mkldnn_memory_t result;
1416  error::wrap_c_api(mkldnn_memory_create(&result, &md.data,
1417  aengine.get(), ahandle), "could not create a memory");
1418  reset(result);
1419  }

1426  : memory(md, aengine, MKLDNN_MEMORY_ALLOCATE) {}

1432  "could not get memory descriptor from a memory");
1433  return desc(*cdesc);

1800 struct primitive_desc : public handle<mkldnn_primitive_desc_t> {
1801  primitive_desc() = default;
1802 
1806  primitive_desc(const_mkldnn_op_desc_t desc, const primitive_attr *attr,
1807  const engine &e, const_mkldnn_primitive_desc_t hint_fwd_pd) {
1808  mkldnn_primitive_desc_iterator_t iterator = nullptr;
1809  mkldnn_status_t status = mkldnn_primitive_desc_iterator_create(
1810  &iterator, desc, attr ? attr->get() : nullptr, e.get(),
1811  hint_fwd_pd);
1812  error::wrap_c_api(status,
1813  "could not create a primitive descriptor iterator");
1814  pd_iterator.reset(iterator);
1815  fetch_impl();
1816  }
1817 
1818  engine get_engine() { return engine::query(*this); }
1819 
1820  primitive_attr get_primitive_attr() const {
1821  const_mkldnn_primitive_attr_t const_cattr;
1822  error::wrap_c_api(mkldnn_primitive_desc_get_attr(get(), &const_cattr),
1823  "could not get attributes");
1824  mkldnn_primitive_attr_t cattr;
1825  error::wrap_c_api(mkldnn_primitive_attr_clone(&cattr, const_cattr),
1826  "could not clone attributes");
1827 
1828  primitive_attr attr;
1829  attr.reset(cattr);
1830  return attr;
1831  }
1832 
1834  const char *impl_info_str() const {
1835  const char *res;
1836  error::wrap_c_api(mkldnn_primitive_desc_query(get(),
1837  mkldnn_query_impl_info_str, 0, &res),
1838  "could not query implementation info string");
1839  return res;
1840  }
1841 
1843  memory::dim query_s64(query q) const {
1844  memory::dim res;
1845  mkldnn_status_t status = mkldnn_primitive_desc_query(get(),
1846  mkldnn::convert_to_c(q), 0, &res);
1847  return status == mkldnn_success ? res : 0;
1848  }
1849 
1856  bool next_impl() {
1857  mkldnn_status_t status = mkldnn_primitive_desc_iterator_next(
1858  pd_iterator.get());
1859  if (status == mkldnn_iterator_ends) return false;
1860  error::wrap_c_api(status, "primitive descriptor iterator next failed");
1861 
1862  fetch_impl();
1863  return true;
1864  }
1865 
1867  memory::desc query_md(query what, int idx = 0) const {
1868  std::vector<query> valid_q{ query::src_md, query::diff_src_md,
1869  query::weights_md, query::diff_weights_md, query::dst_md,
1870  query::diff_dst_md, query::workspace_md, query::scratchpad_md };
1871  if (!std::any_of(valid_q.cbegin(), valid_q.cend(),
1872  [=](query q) { return what == q; }))
1873  throw error(mkldnn_invalid_arguments, "invalid memory query");
1874 
1875  const mkldnn_memory_desc_t *cdesc = mkldnn_primitive_desc_query_md(
1876  get(), mkldnn::convert_to_c(what), idx);
1877  return memory::desc(*cdesc);
1878  }
1879 
1884  memory::desc scratchpad_desc() const {
1885  return query_md(query::scratchpad_md, 0);
1886  }
1887 
1888  private:
1889  handle<mkldnn_primitive_desc_iterator_t> pd_iterator;
1890  void fetch_impl() {
1891  mkldnn_primitive_desc_t pd = mkldnn_primitive_desc_iterator_fetch(
1892  pd_iterator.get());
1893  error::wrap_c_api(pd != nullptr ? mkldnn_success : mkldnn_runtime_error,
1894  "could not fetch a primitive descriptor from the iterator");
1895  reset(pd);
1896  }
1897 };
